---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Ui.astro';
---

<Base title="Media">
  <h1>Media</h1>
  <p>
    Aspect-ratio thumbs that crop to fill, a server-rendered initials fallback
    for the no-image path, tonal skeletons, and captioned figures. Zero radius,
    zero borders — the box is a tonal slot.
  </p>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Thumb ratios</h2>
    <p>
      A <code>.mk-thumb</code> sets the aspect ratio and crops its
      <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> with <code>object-fit: cover</code>. Default is a
      poster (2/3); <code>--square</code> is 1/1 and <code>--video</code> is
      16/9.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">S</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">poster · 2/3</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb mk-thumb--square">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">T</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">square · 1/1</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb mk-thumb--video">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">P</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">video · 16/9</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <pre><code>&lt;div class="mk-thumb"&gt;
  &lt;img src="/poster.jpg" alt="Severance" /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="mk-thumb mk-thumb--square"&gt;…&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="mk-thumb mk-thumb--video"&gt;…&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Initials fallback</h2>
    <p>
      The no-image path. tv-tracker renders <code>.mk-thumb__fallback</code> on
      the server when a poster is missing — it fills the box with a deeper tonal
      surface and a single large mono initial. No image request, no layout
      shift.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">S</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">Severance</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">A</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">Andor</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">T</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cap">The Bear</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <pre><code>&lt;div class="mk-thumb"&gt;
  &lt;div class="mk-thumb__fallback"&gt;S&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Skeleton</h2>
    <p>
      A tonal shimmer for loading state — gradient sweep between surface-2 and
      surface-3, guarded by <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> (static
      surface-2 when reduced). Drop one inside a thumb, or use
      <code>--text</code> for line shims.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="ratio-cell">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-skeleton"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lines">
        <div class="mk-skeleton mk-skeleton--text" style="width: 70%"></div>
        <div class="mk-skeleton mk-skeleton--text" style="width: 45%"></div>
        <div class="mk-skeleton mk-skeleton--text" style="width: 90%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <pre><code>&lt;div class="mk-thumb"&gt;
  &lt;div class="mk-skeleton"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="mk-skeleton mk-skeleton--text" style="width: 70%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Figure with caption</h2>
    <p>
      Wrap media in <code>.mk-figure</code> for a muted, small caption beneath.
      No chrome — only the caption is styled.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <figure class="mk-figure" style="max-width: 9rem">
        <div class="mk-thumb">
          <div class="mk-thumb__fallback">S</div>
        </div>
        <figcaption>Severance — s2e1, aired Jan 2026.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
    <pre><code>&lt;figure class="mk-figure"&gt;
  &lt;div class="mk-thumb"&gt;
    &lt;img src="/poster.jpg" alt="Severance" /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;figcaption&gt;Severance — s2e1, aired Jan 2026.&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Poster grid</h2>
    <p>
      Grids are the app's problem, not the library's — there is no
      <code>.mk-grid</code>. Lay thumbs out with your own CSS grid; the page-local
      style below is the whole recipe.
    </p>
    <div class="poster-grid">
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-thumb__fallback">S</div></div>
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-thumb__fallback">A</div></div>
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-thumb__fallback">T</div></div>
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-thumb__fallback">F</div></div>
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-thumb__fallback">D</div></div>
      <div class="mk-thumb"><div class="mk-skeleton"></div></div>
    </div>
    <pre><code>&lt;ul class="poster-grid"&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;div class="mk-thumb"&gt;…&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

/* app CSS — not shipped by the library */
.poster-grid &#123;
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--mk-space-3);
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(7rem, 1fr));
&#125;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <style>
    section.mk-card + section.mk-card {
      margin-top: var(--mk-space-5);
    }

    .row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: var(--mk-space-4);
    }

    .ratio-cell {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--mk-space-2);
      width: 8rem;
    }

    .ratio-cell .cap,
    .cap {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--mk-text-xs);
      color: var(--mk-color-text-muted);
    }

    .lines {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--mk-space-2);
      flex: 1;
      min-width: 12rem;
    }

    /* Poster grid is page-local on purpose — the library ships no grid. */
    .poster-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--mk-space-3);
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(7rem, 1fr));
    }

    pre {
      margin-top: var(--mk-space-4);
      padding: var(--mk-space-3) var(--mk-space-4);
      background: var(--mk-color-surface-2);
      color: var(--mk-color-text);
      font-size: var(--mk-text-xs);
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
